===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ojp|ja|sort=ぬ}}.  Root of the {{etyl|ojp|-}} verb {{term|lang=ja|ぬる|tr=nuru||to become loose; to become wet}} and modern {{etyl|ja|-|}} {{term|lang=ja|濡れる|tr=nureru||to become wet}}, adverb {{term|lang=ja|ぬるぬる|tr=nurunuru||loosely; lukewarmly; oozingly}}.

May be cognate with {{etyl|ko|-}} {{term|lang=ko|늪|tr=neup||swamp, bog, marsh}}, {{etyl|mn|-}} {{term|lang=mn|нам|tr=nam||low-lying}}, {{term|lang=mn|намаг|tr=namag||swamp, bog, marsh}}, {{term|lang=mn|норох|tr=norokh||to become wet}}.

Generally only used in compounds in modern {{etyl|ja|-}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

